@Wildtruc
I use Linux. Linux bundle dont have tor (Windows bundle have). I dont have Tor installed on my system. I only downloaded from Tor page, Tor browser and unpack it in my personal folder (so my only way to use tor is tor browser). When I command `./ZeroNet.sh` it open in Firefox (my default browser and only browser installed on my system). I want to use ZeroNet only in Tor browser (which is not installed on my system like Firefox but is located in one of my personal folders). If I open Tor browser first, and then command `./ZeroNet.sh` it open Firefox with 0net page. When I close firefox after that and open 0net page in tor browser it dont use Tor. But if I open first Tor browser and then command `./ZeroNet.sh --tor_proxy 127.0.0.1:9150 --tor_controller 127.0.0.1:9151` its open firefox with working Tor (but, if I dont open Tor browser first it open firefox without tor). But when I command `./ZeroNet`, I want to open only Tor Browser (not firefox) with enabled Tor in 0net pages.
I clicked this page you post, but I didnt see my IP there.
@basxto
Thanks, but I have little problem with this. What command I must use, if my Tor browser is located in `/home/antyhrabia/Internetthings/tor-browser_pl` - and there is Tor browser file and browser folder? Command
`./Zeronet --open_browser /home/antyhrabia/Internetthings/tor-browser_pl/Browser/start-tor-browser` didnt work.

